{"sections":[],"abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"Sets strict POSIX mode."}],"variants":[{"paths":["\/documentation\/glib\/optioncontext\/set(strictposix:)"],"traits":[{"interfaceLanguage":"swift"}]}],"metadata":{"externalID":"s:4GLib21OptionContextProtocolPAAE3set11strictPosixySb_tF::SYNTHESIZED::s:4GLib13OptionContextC","modules":[{"name":"GLib"}],"title":"set(strictPosix:)","role":"symbol","fragments":[{"text":"func","kind":"keyword"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"kind":"identifier","text":"set"},{"kind":"text","text":"("},{"kind":"externalParam","text":"strictPosix"},{"text":": ","kind":"text"},{"text":"Bool","preciseIdentifier":"s:Sb","kind":"typeIdentifier"},{"text":")","kind":"text"}],"extendedModule":"GLib","symbolKind":"method","roleHeading":"Instance Method"},"hierarchy":{"paths":[["doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib","doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/OptionContext","doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/OptionContext\/OptionContextProtocol-Implementations"]]},"primaryContentSections":[{"kind":"declarations","declarations":[{"languages":["swift"],"platforms":["macOS"],"tokens":[{"kind":"keyword","text":"func"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"text":"set","kind":"identifier"},{"kind":"text","text":"("},{"text":"strictPosix","kind":"externalParam"},{"kind":"text","text":": "},{"kind":"typeIdentifier","preciseIdentifier":"s:Sb","text":"Bool"},{"kind":"text","text":")"}]}]},{"content":[{"type":"heading","anchor":"discussion","level":2,"text":"Discussion"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"By default, this mode is disabled.","type":"text"}]},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"In strict POSIX mode, the first non-argument parameter encountered"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"(eg: filename) terminates argument processing.  Remaining arguments"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"are treated as non-options and are not attempted to be parsed."}],"type":"paragraph"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"If strict POSIX mode is disabled then parsing is done in the GNU way"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"where option arguments can be freely mixed with non-options.","type":"text"}]},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"As an example, consider “ls foo -l”.  With GNU style parsing, this","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"will list “foo” in long mode.  In strict POSIX style, this will list"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"the files named “foo” and “-l”.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"It may be useful to force strict POSIX mode when creating “verb"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"style” command line tools.  For example, the “gsettings” command line","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"tool supports the global option “–schemadir” as well as many","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"subcommands (“get”, “set”, etc.) which each have their own set of","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"arguments.  Using strict POSIX mode will allow parsing the global"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"options up to the verb name while leaving the remaining options to be"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"parsed by the relevant subcommand (which can be determined by"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"examining the verb name, which should be present in argv[1] after"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"parsing)."}],"type":"paragraph"}],"kind":"content"}],"kind":"symbol","schemaVersion":{"minor":3,"major":0,"patch":0},"identifier":{"url":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/OptionContext\/set(strictPosix:)","interfaceLanguage":"swift"},"references":{"doc://GLib/documentation/GLib/OptionContext":{"role":"symbol","identifier":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/OptionContext","abstract":[{"text":"A ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"GOptionContext"},{"text":" struct defines which options","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"are accepted by the commandline option parser. The struct has only private","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"fields and should not be directly accessed.","type":"text"}],"navigatorTitle":[{"text":"OptionContext","kind":"identifier"}],"title":"OptionContext","url":"\/documentation\/glib\/optioncontext","type":"topic","kind":"symbol","fragments":[{"kind":"keyword","text":"class"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"kind":"identifier","text":"OptionContext"}]},"doc://GLib/documentation/GLib":{"url":"\/documentation\/glib","kind":"symbol","title":"GLib","abstract":[],"type":"topic","identifier":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib","role":"collection"},"doc://GLib/documentation/GLib/OptionContext/OptionContextProtocol-Implementations":{"role":"collectionGroup","identifier":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/OptionContext\/OptionContextProtocol-Implementations","abstract":[],"title":"OptionContextProtocol Implementations","url":"\/documentation\/glib\/optioncontext\/optioncontextprotocol-implementations","type":"topic","kind":"article"},"doc://GLib/documentation/GLib/OptionContext/set(strictPosix:)":{"abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"Sets strict POSIX mode."}],"type":"topic","identifier":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/OptionContext\/set(strictPosix:)","kind":"symbol","fragments":[{"kind":"keyword","text":"func"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"text":"set","kind":"identifier"},{"text":"(","kind":"text"},{"text":"strictPosix","kind":"externalParam"},{"text":": ","kind":"text"},{"kind":"typeIdentifier","preciseIdentifier":"s:Sb","text":"Bool"},{"text":")","kind":"text"}],"role":"symbol","title":"set(strictPosix:)","url":"\/documentation\/glib\/optioncontext\/set(strictposix:)"}}}